      "id": "filing-calendar-2026",
      "topic": "2026 Filing Calendar & Deadlines",
      "category": "Federal Tax",
      "content": "Quarterly estimated tax due dates: Q1 Apr 15, Q2 Jun 15, Q3 Sep 15, Q4 Jan 15 (following year). Form 1120 corporate return: Apr 15. Florida F-1120 corporate income/franchise: May 1 (for calendar-year filers). Verify against current IRS Pub 509 and FL DOR before agent acts on a deadline.",
      "status": "draft",
      "sourceDocs": ["IRS Pub 509", "FL DOR website"],
      "lastUpdated": "2026-05-07"
    },
    {
      "id": "fl-state-tax",
      "topic": "Florida State Tax Rules",
      "category": "State Tax",
      "content": "FL has no state personal income tax. FL corporate income/franchise tax: 5.5% (subject to revisions). FL sales tax: 6% statewide + county surtax. Verify current rates against FL DOR before quoting a number to a partner or candidate.",
      "status": "draft",
      "sourceDocs": ["FL DOR rates page"],
      "lastUpdated": "2026-05-07"
    },
